  calories: 1380 kcal
  fat: 85 g
  saturated fat: 20 g
  carbohydrates: 89 g
  sugar: 10 g
  protein: 58 g
  fiber: 9 g
  sodium: 1340 mg
course: main course
servings: 2
time required: 35 minutes
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/spring-chicken-pesto-rigatoni-624c447ad734d42cde0d5c21
cuisine: North America
---

Bring a #medium pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Halve @scallions{4} crosswise, separating whites from greens. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}.

Heat a #large dry pan{} over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites and scallion greens; cook ~{1-2%minutes} per side, until charred.

> Scallion greens will cook faster than scallion whites. Once greens are charred, remove from pan and continue cooking whites.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{}. Once cool enough to handle, roughly chop.

Slice @bacon{4%ounce} crosswise into 1/4-inch pieces.

Heat dry pan used for scallions over medium-high heat. Add bacon in an even layer; cook undisturbed, until crispy on bottom, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir bacon; cook, stirring occasionally and adjusting heat if browning too quickly, until crispy, ~{2-5%minutes} more.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #paper-towel-lined plate{}. Reserve bacon fat in pan. Once cool enough to handle, crumble bacon into smaller pieces.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with @garlic powder{1%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Once pan used for bacon has cooled slightly, heat reserved bacon fat over medium heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer to a cutting board. Wipe out pan.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp} in same pan over medium heat. Add @almonds{1%ounce} and cook, stirring occasionally, until golden, ~{1-2%minutes}. Turn off heat and set aside.

Once water is boiling, add @rigatoni pasta{6%ounce} to #pot{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until almost al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Reserve 1/2 cup pasta cooking water, then drain and return to pot.

While pasta cooks, place @ricotta cheese{4%ounce} in a #small bowl{}. Season with @olive oil{1%tbsp}, lemon zest from half the lemon to taste, and a pinch of salt and pepper. Stir to combine.

> To save on cleanup, mix ricotta directly in cup.

Add @spinach{5%ounce}, @pesto{1/2%cup}, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, juice from half the lemon, and 1/4 cup reserved pasta cooking water to pot with pasta. Toss until spinach is wilted and pasta is al dente. If needed, stir in more reserved cooking water a splash at a time until pasta is thoroughly coated in sauce.

Stir in almonds and chopped scallions. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Slice chicken crosswise.

Divide pasta between #bowls{} and top with chicken. Dollop with seasoned ricotta and sprinkle with crumbled bacon. Season with pepper. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.